<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870626-0177 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Capital Holding Corp.</HL><DD> 06/26/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CPH </IN><TEXT>   CAPITAL HOLDING CORP., Louisville, Ky., said it signed a five-year, $300 million agreement with 19 U.S. and international financial institutions, arranged by Chase Investment Bank and Chemical Bank International Group. Capital Holdings, a financial services and insurance concern, said the agreement includes a revolving credit option, a Euronote issuance option and a short-term advances option. The company said funds will be used for general purposes. </TEXT></DOC>